1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:26,960
If you want Na back, give me the one who
extorted money by tomorrow before sunset.

2
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:31,520
<i>You're too late, Pinanong.</i>

3
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:34,800
So I burnt him alive,
taking revenge for you in one go.

4
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:38,600
I never believed you were truly evil,

5
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:40,640
but now, I'm sure you are.

6
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:42,920
<i>I'm sorry I couldn't protect you.</i>

7
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,320
I never hated you, Mr. Yai.

8
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:53,000
Do you need my help?

9
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:53,960
Here.

10
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:10,320
Who taught you that?

11
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:13,240
My mom.

12
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:16,320
It's rare to find someone this young
who can do that.

13
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:19,680
Modern technologies
make things a lot easier.

14
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:23,320
And when people fall in love,
they just run away together.

15
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,760
Well, there's nothing going on
between me and Mr. Yai.

16
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:30,960
Then why did you let him
take advantage of you?

17
00:03:31,040 --> 00:03:32,320
Let me tell you something.

18
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:35,440
There's a thin line
between being good and being stupid.

19
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:38,560
But I don't think you're stupid.

20
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:41,200
Pin. Pin.

21
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:43,560
Oh, there you are.

22
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:45,320
Did you put my woman to work, Chief?

23
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:47,600
- Ugh. Come here, Pin.
- Hey, hey.

24
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:48,800
Whoa, whoa.

25
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:53,440
I'm making sour soup
with green papaya, your favorite.

26
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:02,000
That's it.

27
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,960
Chief, what did you say
to incite my woman?

28
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:05,160
She's resisting now.

29
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:06,320
I didn't incite her.

30
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:09,720
I just told her that
men usually lie to get what they want

31
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,400
and are sometimes selfish.

32
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:14,680
So she should just cut
the dead weight and toss it.

33
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,200
Isn't that too brutal?

34
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,959
Hey.

35
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,160
While you're here,

36
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,960
if you want to eat something,
help yourself.

37
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,920
We grow
all our own ingredients right here.

38
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,120
You did all this all by yourself, Chief?

39
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:31,160
With a fierce attitude like that,
what man would ever dare to marry you?

40
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:34,160
A useless husband is a waste of my energy.

41
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:35,160
You too.

42
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:39,240
If you want to be useful,
go help me chop some more firewood.

43
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,520
Just shut up and go.

44
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:42,160
Chief.

45
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:50,680
What? You're actually making me work?

46
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:56,560
This morning, I was told that the gunmen
who chased you have exited the territory.

47
00:04:57,080 --> 00:04:58,000
What about my truck?

48
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,080
It wasn't damaged.

49
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:01,320
I had someone drive it to the mechanic.

50
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:03,160
They'll be back soon.

51
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:06,160
This was in that truck.

52
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:08,840
Thank you, Chief.

53
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:12,720
Actually, there weren't
any criminals in this area.

54
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:15,200
Did you make any enemies anywhere?

55
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:18,320
Don't ask me where I made enemies.

56
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:21,640
You'll be surprised by how many there are,
because they're everywhere I go.

57
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:24,120
You know that,
and still want to have a wife?

58
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:28,120
For a woman, marriage is a lifelong
commitment, not a trivial matter.

59
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:33,040
If you can't step up, don't even bother.

60
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:57,240
Pin.

61
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:59,320
I'm sorry.

62
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:08,160
There's a thin line
between being good and being stupid.

63
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,760
You're stupid,

64
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:16,520
incredibly stupid, Pinanong.

65
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,920
Why do you always
let Tatsanee pick on you?

66
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,080
Just fight back.

67
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,440
No.

68
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:50,840
Mom would flog me.

69
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:53,600
She said Madam was kind to us.

70
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:56,360
I must tolerate Ms. Nee even if it hurts.

71
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:57,880
You're stupid.

72
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:17,920
Feeling better?

73
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:20,640
Your boogers are all over my shirt.

74
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,720
I'm feeling better.

75
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:26,360
Thank you.

76
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:29,760
I don't understand.

77
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:33,080
After everything he did to you,
you still cry over him.

78
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,400
Haven't you ever loved anyone?

79
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:38,480
I have.

80
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:42,000
But that girl was totally blind.

81
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:43,920
She fell for some other guy.

82
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:47,880
So how did you move on from her?

83
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:52,160
I don't need to.

84
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:56,520
But I'll take her from him no matter what.

85
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:02,520
Being a third wheel?

86
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,840
You'll all just end up suffering.

87
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:10,200
You aren't fighting for Tatsana

88
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:13,160
because you're just not that into him.

89
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,400
I'm not trying to win
against anyone, unlike you.

90
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,480
You're just as dumb
as your tortoise, Tuem.

91
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,160
Yes.

92
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,760
All this time, I've been stupid.

93
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:37,039
But from this moment on,

94
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:41,120
I won't shed a tear
because of Mr. Na anymore.

95
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:46,480
Thank you, Mr. Yai,

96
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:49,360
for freeing me
from hopes that led nowhere.

97
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:38,320
Marry her?

98
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:44,680
What about Mr. Yai?

99
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:47,840
If he comes back…

100
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:53,040
He won't be coming back,
neither he nor Pin.

101
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:55,160
What do you mean by that?

102
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:57,680
Don't worry about that.

103
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:59,120
Let's just say,

104
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:03,760
I won't ever let anyone stand in the way
of your success and happiness.

105
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:05,880
My Na

106
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:09,000
will have wealth, love,

107
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:11,640
and respectable status,

108
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:14,080
or I won't be at peace.

109
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:21,200
Thank you. I love you the most.

110
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:24,760
You're the one I love the most too.

111
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:28,680
We're going to Bangkok soon,
to formally propose to On.

112
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:32,120
Yes.

113
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,080
- Let's get ready.
- Right.

114
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:52,760
TEERA: THE HIRED GUNS ARE BACK

115
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:56,360
Pay them as agreed.

116
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,600
Is it done?

117
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:12,720
They're dead.

118
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:15,480
Where are the bodies?

119
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:19,520
Already burnt on tires and buried.

120
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:20,720
What else do you want?

121
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:23,880
Hurry up and pay us the other half.

122
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,440
We need to lay low.

123
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:27,720
Of course. I've prepared it.

124
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:29,920
Go get the money.

125
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:32,080
Kan, give it to them.

126
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:33,760
Hey, what the hell?

127
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:37,040
Hey!

128
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:39,280
Follow him.

129
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:07,960
There was probably a fight here.

130
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:09,760
Multiple people were involved.

131
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:11,680
But I don't know who they are.

132
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:22,760
Bullet shells.

133
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:25,320
If someone was trying to kill Mr. Yai…

134
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:29,360
What about Pin? Will she be okay?

135
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,520
You'll pay for it.

136
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:36,400
Bandit Yai threw his life away
all because of Pin.

137
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:37,760
Don't you dare blame Pin.

138
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,840
Don't blame Mr. Yai either.

139
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:42,520
Hey, that's enough. Enough!

140
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:44,920
Stop fighting.

141
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:47,680
This is a matter of life and death.

142
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:50,400
We need to report this to the police now.

143
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,520
If anything happens to Pin,

144
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:54,160
you're dead.

145
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:09,120
Stir-fried ivy gourd leaves with eggs
and fried fish with herbs.

146
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:11,560
These are both of my favorites!

147
00:13:13,560 --> 00:13:16,400
Hey. Are you a cripple or what?

148
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:19,160
Okay, okay.

149
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:20,480
You didn't need to be so harsh, Chief.

150
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:23,800
It's okay. It's my duty.

151
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:25,440
Let me tell you.

152
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:29,160
This house has no maids,
no masters, and no slaves.

153
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:31,400
I don't feel like I'm a slave at all.

154
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:34,640
I'm just happy every time
I can repay someone's kindness.

155
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:38,880
It's good to be grateful,
but you also need to know good from bad.

156
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:41,960
Most importantly, you should be able
to tell right from wrong.

157
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:45,360
That's spot on.

158
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:47,920
Please help rewire
this dumb girl's mindset, Chief.

159
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:51,400
She's so blinded by gratitude
that she's lost all common sense.

160
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,760
Huh?

161
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:55,240
Who would be ungrateful like you?

162
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:58,080
You were angry
with your father for years, right?

163
00:13:58,840 --> 00:13:59,960
Well?

164
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:02,760
Let's eat. Dig in.

165
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:03,760
Come on.

166
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:06,320
Have some. You're old now. You need this.

167
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:08,240
- Enough.
- And you.

168
00:14:08,880 --> 00:14:10,360
You need veggies

169
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:13,440
and protein to boost your brainpower.

170
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:14,800
Here, eat them.

171
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:31,160
Hey.

172
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:34,440
Hey.

173
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:37,920
Who the hell are you?

174
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:39,960
How did you get into the farm?

175
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:43,840
Or could he be the one
who ambushed Mr. Yai?

176
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:10,080
<i>Moon, oh, moon</i>

177
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:13,440
<i>I wish for rice and curry</i>

178
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:16,360
<i>I wish for a copper ring</i>

179
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:19,840
<i>For my little one's hand</i>

180
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:24,360
<i>I wish for an elephant, for a steed</i>

181
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:27,360
<i>For my little one to ride on</i>

182
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:34,720
Mom.

183
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:39,760
Mom.

184
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:43,600
Mom.

185
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:46,000
Mom.

186
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,840
Mom.

187
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:52,160
Mom.

188
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:51,640
Mom.

189
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:53,400
Mom…

190
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:55,480
Please don't go. Mom.

191
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:57,640
Don't go.

192
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:01,080
Mom, don't leave me.

193
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:02,840
Mom…

194
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:04,480
Mom.

195
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:07,079
- Mom, don't leave me.
- Mr. Yai?

196
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:09,920
Mom… Mom…

197
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:12,160
Mom. Don't leave me yet.

198
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:14,520
Mom. Please don't leave me.

199
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:15,440
Mr. Yai.

200
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:17,319
- Mom, don't leave me.
- Mr. Yai.

201
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,720
- Mom. Mom.
- Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai.

202
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:24,760
Pin?

203
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:31,800
Wait, did you…

204
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,440
Were you trying to do it
while I was asleep?

205
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:36,600
No.

206
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:40,200
It's cold,
so I was bringing you a blanket.

207
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:44,840
Mr. Yai, did you have a nightmare?

208
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:49,560
No, I was chasing
a curvy girl in my dream.

209
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:51,440
Thanks for ruining the mood.

210
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:55,400
Then why do I see tears?

211
00:17:57,480 --> 00:17:58,480
Tears?

212
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:00,800
What tears?

213
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:02,720
There's nothing.

214
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:04,040
It's so hot, I'm dripping with sweat.

215
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:05,560
Who said it's cold?

216
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:12,120
Please go back to sleep.

217
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:29,600
What are you doing in here, Mr. Yai?

218
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:30,800
The net is all torn apart.

219
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:32,320
The weather's hot.

220
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:34,800
The mosquitoes are huge.
How am I supposed to sleep?

221
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:39,280
- Then I'll go sleep outside instead.
- No.

222
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,720
What if you run away?

223
00:18:43,040 --> 00:18:46,480
Then just tie my hands and feet.

224
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:49,040
Being sarcastic?
You think I won't do that?

225
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:50,240
Come here.

226
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:25,440
Still not asleep?

227
00:19:25,520 --> 00:19:27,240
Or do you want me to sleep there with you?

228
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:32,840
I miss my mom.

229
00:19:39,560 --> 00:19:41,920
You miss your mom too, right?

230
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:46,720
She passed away before I even turned 10.

231
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:53,560
I remember that she was so beautiful

232
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:55,960
and could sing really well.

233
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,000
I loved when she sang me a lullaby.

234
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:06,800
What song did she sing?

235
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:09,600
Was it this one?

236
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:13,920
<i>Moon, oh, moon</i>

237
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:16,960
<i>I wish for rice and curry</i>

238
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:18,680
That's enough.

239
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:21,840
With your raspy voice,
I might have nightmares.

240
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:24,320
I don't believe

241
00:20:25,680 --> 00:20:27,680
that you're truly cruel

242
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:30,280
the way you pretend to be
in front of everyone.

243
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:32,360
And I don't believe

244
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,600
that you murdered Pha

245
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:38,440
or that you have been robbing
or killing anyone.

246
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:46,040
Are you trying to talk me out of taking
action against you and Krongsuk's gang?

247
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:48,560
You're taking advantage
of my kindness, huh?

248
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:49,880
I'm not.

249
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:53,520
If you're disrespecting me,

250
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:57,720
then I might have to show you how
ruthless and insatiable Bandit Yai can be.

251
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,520
We're not going to sleep tonight, Pin.

252
00:21:00,360 --> 00:21:02,520
I won't say anything anymore. I'll stop.

253
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:21,840
LOVE
LITTLE SHEPHERD

254
00:21:29,640 --> 00:21:30,600
Hello, Dad.

255
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:32,200
Can you not scold me now?

256
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:33,560
I'm too exhausted.

257
00:21:35,840 --> 00:21:36,840
Yai?

258
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:41,920
You jerk. I thought you were a goner.

259
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:45,440
Where did you disappear to?

260
00:21:45,520 --> 00:21:48,120
Someone sent gunmen
to get rid of Pin and I,

261
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:51,640
so I had to come hide at a safehouse
of someone I can trust.

262
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:55,960
What? Send me the photo.

263
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:04,800
Yes.

264
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:07,320
That was him. And where is he now?

265
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:10,840
Keep him there.

266
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:12,720
I'll pry the truth out of him myself.

267
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:28,120
We've already given him first aid,
but his wounds are severe.

268
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:31,160
He'll need to be transferred
to the provincial hospital.

269
00:22:37,960 --> 00:22:39,000
Jom.

270
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:40,600
Mr. Yai?

271
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:43,720
What about Pin? Where is she?

272
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:45,240
Your Pin is safe.

273
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:48,280
So did the hitman say anything yet?

274
00:22:48,360 --> 00:22:51,920
If we don't take him to the hospital now,
he won't be able to speak again.

275
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:06,440
Sir! Don't do that!

276
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:07,600
Let go! Get off me!

277
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:09,400
Sir!

278
00:23:09,480 --> 00:23:12,160
Help! Help! Sir!

279
00:23:14,480 --> 00:23:16,680
Yai. Yai!

280
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,680
Stop running. Stop!

281
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:39,200
Hey, my bike!

282
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:42,520
My bike! Hey!

283
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:43,440
Hey!

284
00:24:11,280 --> 00:24:12,280
You didn't see the body?

285
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:14,680
Then how can you be sure he's dead?

286
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:16,360
Well, Boss.

287
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:19,600
We emptied our clips into him.

288
00:24:19,680 --> 00:24:22,560
After shots like that,
there's no way he could survive, Boss.

289
00:24:22,640 --> 00:24:26,760
But if the body surfaces,
the police will trace it back to us.

290
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,960
Hey, let me ask you something.

291
00:24:30,040 --> 00:24:33,440
If you just keep your mouth shut
about this, will the police know?

292
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:36,200
Idiot.

293
00:24:37,840 --> 00:24:40,280
Both of you, find the body.

294
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:43,560
Then, ask around
to see if anyone saw anything.

295
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:44,800
Yes, Boss.

296
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:45,960
Let's go.

297
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:55,800
How are things looking over there?

298
00:24:55,880 --> 00:24:56,880
Everything okay?

299
00:24:58,320 --> 00:24:59,320
Hey.

300
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:03,280
Are you hiring a hit on someone, Manager?

301
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,360
Mr. Yai?

302
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:16,560
Hey, Aunt Un.

303
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:20,680
I bet Madam didn't send
anyone to save Pin.

304
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:23,960
Hey, if you can't say something good,
then be quiet!

305
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:28,600
Aunt Un, I'm worried about Pin too.

306
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:30,600
She was gone all night.

307
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:33,520
Who knows if Mr. Yai
would do anything to her?

308
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:38,520
- Mom.
- Pin?

309
00:25:38,600 --> 00:25:39,520
Pin?

310
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:41,760
Pin.

311
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:44,040
Are you okay?

312
00:25:44,120 --> 00:25:46,400
Yai didn't do anything to you, right?

313
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:49,000
No, he didn't hurt me.

314
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:51,640
See, Noi?

315
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:54,440
I told you Madam really sent
someone to save Pin.

316
00:25:54,960 --> 00:25:57,640
So what happened?
Did the police take Yai in?

317
00:25:57,720 --> 00:26:00,880
Mr. Yai and I were being hunted by gunmen.

318
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:03,360
And the one who helped us
wasn't sent by Madam.

319
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:05,480
It was the village chief
who Mr. Yai knows.

320
00:26:06,080 --> 00:26:08,920
There. I knew it. I was right.

321
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:12,120
And… who were the ones hunting you?

322
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:16,720
Who else could it be behind it
besides your beloved Madam, Aunt Un?

323
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:20,120
She sent Pin to exchange for Na

324
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:22,640
and sent people after me and Pin
to get rid of both of us.

325
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:24,440
Two birds with one stone.

326
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:26,720
So damn smart.

327
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:29,160
That's impossible. I don't believe you.

328
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:32,480
Only a vile thief like you
would think of killing someone.

329
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:35,880
Then ask this manager
who is truly the most vile.

330
00:26:37,360 --> 00:26:38,280
Talk.

331
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:39,920
What am I supposed to talk about?

332
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:45,200
Let me remind you only once

333
00:26:45,280 --> 00:26:47,320
about the money missing from the accounts

334
00:26:48,120 --> 00:26:52,920
and about the fact that you sent gunmen
to silence me and Pinanong.

335
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:55,240
Did Madam Krongsuk order you to do that?

336
00:27:05,240 --> 00:27:07,320
Win, shoot his leg.

337
00:27:09,080 --> 00:27:11,920
- Sorry, Manager. I must follow orders.
- Hey.

338
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:14,320
Please don't take it this far, Mr. Yai.

339
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:18,080
Pin, did you forget the moment we ran
to save ourselves from those gunmen?

340
00:27:18,160 --> 00:27:20,720
Without Chief Yam's help,
we would have met our maker by now.

341
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:27,120
About the money, Madam told me
to cover everything up for Pin,

342
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:29,200
so why would she send someone after you?

343
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:30,160
Shoot.

344
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:31,120
Hey, hey.

345
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:33,040
Hey, wait. Jom's calling.

346
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:38,400
Good. If you don't want to talk, fine.

347
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:41,200
Because I caught a wounded hitman.

348
00:27:41,280 --> 00:27:43,400
He's in the hospital right now.

349
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:47,360
Once he opens his mouth,
everything will be revealed.

350
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:50,120
Then we'll need to tell the police

351
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:54,280
that he was a criminal raiding the farm
and that we don't know anything else.

352
00:27:55,160 --> 00:27:56,000
What's up?

353
00:27:56,080 --> 00:27:58,440
The hitman died
during the transfer to the hospital.

354
00:27:58,520 --> 00:27:59,560
Now, the police know about it.

355
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:01,840
Jom and Jintana are giving a statement.

356
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:04,800
If the hitman is dead,

357
00:28:04,880 --> 00:28:06,960
then we won't have a way of knowing

358
00:28:07,040 --> 00:28:09,880
if he was only robbing us
or trying to kill us.

359
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:15,880
So, can I get back
to my office now, Mr. Yai?

360
00:28:18,040 --> 00:28:20,000
- Hey.
- Don't think I'll let you off easily.

361
00:28:20,080 --> 00:28:22,360
As long as I still don't know
who ordered my death…

362
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:24,680
Pan, Win,

363
00:28:24,760 --> 00:28:26,600
lock him in the barn for now.

364
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:29,040
Have the workers find Jerd and Kan.

365
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:31,240
Come with me.

366
00:28:31,320 --> 00:28:32,200
Hey, hey. Wait.

367
00:28:32,280 --> 00:28:33,960
You can't just take the law
into your own hands.

368
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:36,840
You scumbag.

369
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:40,000
Pin, come with me. Now.

370
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:45,840
Damn it.

371
00:28:47,040 --> 00:28:48,040
You scumbag.

372
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:58,160
Na and Nee are my niblings.

373
00:28:58,240 --> 00:29:02,800
Both of them were orphans,
but they've always been good kids.

374
00:29:03,320 --> 00:29:06,440
Na has excelled in his studies.

375
00:29:06,520 --> 00:29:07,960
He has won scholarships year after year.

376
00:29:08,040 --> 00:29:11,640
And Nee's currently learning
English and Chinese.

377
00:29:11,720 --> 00:29:15,160
She's deciding between majoring
in business administration or PR.

378
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:19,120
They're both good-looking and smart too.

379
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:20,640
You must be so proud.

380
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:22,680
Yes.

381
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:24,800
I've raised them myself.

382
00:29:25,320 --> 00:29:26,400
Nee.

383
00:29:26,920 --> 00:29:28,080
She complimented you.

384
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:34,360
<i>Xiexie ni.</i>

385
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:35,760
Thank you.

386
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:44,080
I think we should talk
about what we're here for.

387
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:45,960
Of course.

388
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:48,080
The youth are always
in such a rush, right?

389
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:52,160
He's been pressuring me to hurry up and
ask for your daughter's hand in marriage.

390
00:29:54,080 --> 00:29:55,800
Then you can talk to my wife.

391
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:58,080
I have work to do.

392
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,240
Please stay, Dad.

393
00:30:03,280 --> 00:30:04,440
Here.

394
00:30:04,960 --> 00:30:07,720
This is the list of all the dowry items.

395
00:30:17,040 --> 00:30:19,160
All of this?

396
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:20,240
Yes.

397
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:22,240
Is the total too high?

398
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:26,840
No, no. It's appropriate for On.

399
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:31,520
Then we are in agreement?

400
00:30:32,920 --> 00:30:34,960
Yes, of course.

401
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:37,920
Please don't worry about this, Auntie.

402
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:40,560
For the heir to Paisal Farm,

403
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:43,200
this is floor-level.

404
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:47,080
It's basic.

405
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:55,760
You're acting without any consideration
for your daughter at all.

406
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:58,840
You're the one
without consideration for me.

407
00:30:58,920 --> 00:31:01,080
You couldn't wait to sell her off.

408
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:02,920
So it was my fault?

409
00:31:03,440 --> 00:31:07,000
If you hadn't trusted those brown-nosers
who set up a bid-rigging company,

410
00:31:07,080 --> 00:31:10,160
you wouldn't have had to take the fall
and pay the debts alone.

411
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:12,040
I can take care of it myself.

412
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:14,080
Get that country madam out of our house.

413
00:31:14,800 --> 00:31:16,200
Then what are you going to do?

414
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:19,440
Are you just going to lie down and wait
for the bank to declare us bankrupt?

415
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:20,800
Shut your mouth, On.

416
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:21,680
Dear.

417
00:31:22,560 --> 00:31:25,320
I'm the only way out for all of us.

418
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:27,000
Remember that.

419
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:36,360
What did you say?

420
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:38,000
You want me to leave this place?

421
00:31:38,840 --> 00:31:41,080
You know full well what the problem is.

422
00:31:41,160 --> 00:31:43,400
It's not that I want you to go.

423
00:31:43,480 --> 00:31:46,240
But that is the best solution
for everyone.

424
00:31:46,840 --> 00:31:49,640
And if Mr. Yai still wants
to punish someone after you leave,

425
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:51,480
I'll go to prison for you.

426
00:31:51,560 --> 00:31:53,360
I don't have many years left in my life.

427
00:31:54,200 --> 00:31:55,760
Mom.

428
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:57,480
Even if you're willing to die,

429
00:31:57,560 --> 00:32:00,040
Mr. Yai won't back down so easily.

430
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:01,800
I know him well.

431
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:03,560
I don't want to run anymore.

432
00:32:04,160 --> 00:32:05,240
You know him well?

433
00:32:05,760 --> 00:32:07,240
Did you mean…

434
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:09,920
you're his woman now?

435
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:11,800
He's already claimed you, hasn't he?

436
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:13,400
That's not what I meant, Mom.

437
00:32:13,480 --> 00:32:15,440
Mr. Yai didn't do anything to me.

438
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:18,880
He may appear rough and evil,

439
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:21,320
but deep down, he's a true gentleman.

440
00:32:22,080 --> 00:32:25,880
Unlike someone
who looks good on the outside

441
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:28,280
but is actually heartless.

442
00:32:29,240 --> 00:32:30,800
Are you out of your mind?

443
00:32:30,880 --> 00:32:33,600
How could you see someone
so evil as a good man, Pin?!

444
00:32:34,560 --> 00:32:38,160
If he was truly a gentleman,
why would he trade Na for you?

445
00:32:38,760 --> 00:32:40,640
He's manipulating you
into being his plaything.

446
00:32:40,720 --> 00:32:44,320
He would never treat you
as a real, legitimate wife.

447
00:32:45,120 --> 00:32:46,640
If you don't believe in me,

448
00:32:47,560 --> 00:32:50,040
then I don't know
how to convince you anymore.

449
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:55,160
But I'll never leave you
to face all the problems alone.

450
00:33:13,120 --> 00:33:15,720
Pan. Pan!

451
00:33:16,560 --> 00:33:17,680
Pan!

452
00:33:18,720 --> 00:33:20,720
Where is he? Pan.

453
00:33:20,800 --> 00:33:21,960
We need to go see Uncle Pload.

454
00:33:22,040 --> 00:33:23,320
I have something important
to talk to him about.

455
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:25,640
We don't need to go. He's coming here.

456
00:33:26,520 --> 00:33:29,080
What? What did you tell Uncle Pload?

457
00:33:29,880 --> 00:33:31,200
It's all because of you.

458
00:33:31,280 --> 00:33:33,600
You told me to lie to him,
so he was suspicious.

459
00:33:34,840 --> 00:33:38,680
He told me that if I didn't tell
the truth, he'd come and see for himself,

460
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,680
so I had to tell the whole truth.

461
00:33:42,520 --> 00:33:45,000
Fine. So I don't need to explain anything.

462
00:33:45,080 --> 00:33:46,960
And did he tell you
where he'll be staying?

463
00:33:47,040 --> 00:33:50,520
He's coming here,
and he isn't coming alone.

464
00:33:53,080 --> 00:33:54,120
Wait, wait.

465
00:34:06,920 --> 00:34:08,120
What?

466
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:18,480
Hey. Get all the weapons ready.

467
00:34:18,560 --> 00:34:21,000
This time, there will be no compromises.

468
00:34:21,600 --> 00:34:23,679
I will take Paisal Farm.

469
00:34:24,199 --> 00:34:25,920
Don't you want to tell Mr. Yai, Boss?

470
00:34:26,520 --> 00:34:28,480
Mr. Yai's being too soft.

471
00:34:28,560 --> 00:34:31,639
By now, he's likely already fallen
for one of their honey traps

472
00:34:31,719 --> 00:34:33,320
and has forgotten about his revenge.

473
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:37,040
I can't let Mr. Yai
end up like his father.

474
00:34:45,080 --> 00:34:47,239
Boss, someone's blocking our way.

475
00:34:51,080 --> 00:34:52,840
Must be that madam's men.

476
00:34:53,600 --> 00:34:56,120
She knows then. Phong,

477
00:34:56,639 --> 00:34:59,160
drive right through them.

478
00:34:59,240 --> 00:35:00,160
- Yes, Boss.
- Go.

479
00:35:05,480 --> 00:35:06,800
Mr. Yai? Hey, stop.

480
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:22,480
Mr. Yai.

481
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:24,520
Why are you blocking my way?

482
00:35:33,680 --> 00:35:34,720
- Dad.
- Wait, Uncle.

483
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:40,520
You brat.

484
00:35:40,600 --> 00:35:42,480
I couldn't trust you with anything.

485
00:35:42,560 --> 00:35:44,720
How could you leave
Mr. Yai alone like that?

486
00:35:46,760 --> 00:35:48,400
We almost ran over him.

487
00:35:49,240 --> 00:35:51,920
Dad, don't you worry
about your son at all?

488
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:54,280
Yai wouldn't listen.
He wanted to come on his own.

489
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:57,040
He said I don't drive as fast as he wants.

490
00:35:57,120 --> 00:35:59,120
Please don't blame Pan.

491
00:35:59,200 --> 00:36:00,840
It was all my fault.

492
00:36:00,920 --> 00:36:05,000
I stopped him from telling you, so
I rushed to you before things escalated.

493
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:06,160
I don't understand.

494
00:36:07,120 --> 00:36:10,440
Pinanong is
one of Madam Krongsuk's people.

495
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:13,560
She's planning
to use a woman to distract you.

496
00:36:13,640 --> 00:36:15,480
Why can't you see through it?

497
00:36:15,560 --> 00:36:17,480
Pinanong doesn't know anything.

498
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:20,440
Her and I almost got killed
by Madam's men.

499
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:24,000
The Moor has done his duty,
the Moor may go.

500
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:30,560
Madam might think
Pinanong is no longer useful,

501
00:36:31,200 --> 00:36:32,960
so she is trying to silence her

502
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:36,200
to prevent secrets from spreading.

503
00:36:37,280 --> 00:36:38,760
Pinanong was just being used.

504
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:41,160
She would never hate me.

505
00:36:44,240 --> 00:36:45,520
I didn't expect you

506
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:49,320
to eventually fall into their trap too.

507
00:36:51,640 --> 00:36:53,800
I shouldn't have let you come here.

508
00:37:00,120 --> 00:37:01,360
All this vengeance

509
00:37:02,520 --> 00:37:04,440
will be settled today.

510
00:37:17,040 --> 00:37:19,080
Noi, I slept in too late.

511
00:37:19,160 --> 00:37:21,160
Did Mom have breakfast
and take her medicine yet?

512
00:37:21,240 --> 00:37:22,280
Aunt Un's inside.

513
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:23,960
I was about to go get you.

514
00:37:24,040 --> 00:37:25,440
What happened to her?

515
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:38,800
Where is everyone?

516
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:41,200
Does anyone actually work around here?

517
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:42,360
Madam!

518
00:37:43,280 --> 00:37:44,440
Hey.

519
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:45,920
Who are you?

520
00:37:47,320 --> 00:37:49,280
Are you Mr. Tong's men?

521
00:37:50,040 --> 00:37:51,840
I just returned from Bangkok.

522
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:54,120
I've got some money for him for sure.

523
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:55,720
I'll contact him directly.

524
00:37:55,800 --> 00:37:58,040
Na, what's going on?

525
00:37:58,120 --> 00:37:59,400
Who's this Mr. Tong?

526
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:01,120
I have no idea.

527
00:38:07,920 --> 00:38:09,280
Good morning, everyone.

528
00:38:12,400 --> 00:38:13,440
Pload?

529
00:38:14,840 --> 00:38:15,760
Mr. Yai?

530
00:38:16,360 --> 00:38:19,760
They're gonna kill us all this time.

531
00:38:19,840 --> 00:38:21,560
I shouldn't have come back.

532
00:38:24,520 --> 00:38:25,880
Long time no see.

533
00:38:27,320 --> 00:38:28,720
You're beautiful as ever, Madam.

534
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:31,560
You've changed a lot, haven't you?

535
00:38:34,320 --> 00:38:37,240
Why didn't you tell me you were
showing Pload around the farm, Mr. Yai?

536
00:38:37,960 --> 00:38:39,560
So I could have come back sooner.

537
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:43,080
I didn't think I could come back either.

538
00:38:43,160 --> 00:38:46,800
But I was lucky enough
to survive the bullets.

539
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:50,800
Did… Did someone do something to you?

540
00:38:52,120 --> 00:38:53,160
Too bad

541
00:38:53,240 --> 00:38:56,280
the hired gun rushed to Hell first,

542
00:38:57,240 --> 00:38:59,920
so we don't know who ordered the hit.

543
00:39:02,920 --> 00:39:03,800
What about Pin?

544
00:39:03,880 --> 00:39:06,000
Don't you think it's too late
to worry about her?

545
00:39:07,520 --> 00:39:09,160
Why are you even talking to him?

546
00:39:09,240 --> 00:39:10,680
He took you hostage.

547
00:39:10,760 --> 00:39:12,720
Just call the police to take him in.

548
00:39:13,480 --> 00:39:14,600
Na.

549
00:39:14,680 --> 00:39:16,560
Take On to your room.

550
00:39:17,080 --> 00:39:19,960
I have so much to talk about with Mr. Yai.

551
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:22,880
Let… Let me bring her upstairs myself.

552
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:23,800
No need.

553
00:39:24,720 --> 00:39:26,680
Everyone will stay right here.

554
00:39:27,560 --> 00:39:29,200
Let us all be witnesses.

555
00:39:29,800 --> 00:39:31,040
Witnesses?

556
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:33,200
Witnesses to what?

557
00:39:34,920 --> 00:39:37,160
There's no use holding us here.

558
00:39:37,880 --> 00:39:39,160
There's nothing here for you.

559
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:42,000
They're not robbing us, Mom.

560
00:39:42,080 --> 00:39:43,400
How do you know that?

561
00:39:43,480 --> 00:39:45,160
I remember them.

562
00:39:45,240 --> 00:39:47,080
They're Uncle Pload's men.

563
00:39:47,960 --> 00:39:48,840
Huh?

564
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:55,200
Boss told me to come get these two.

565
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:03,360
Witnesses for the formal proposal.

566
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:05,400
Who's proposing to whom?

567
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:09,400
I heard Tatsana
is going to have a wedding,

568
00:40:09,480 --> 00:40:13,080
so I invited Uncle Pload,
my respected elder,

569
00:40:13,160 --> 00:40:15,560
to represent me
in proposing to a woman as well.

570
00:40:16,160 --> 00:40:17,680
Let's have a double wedding

571
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:22,040
and make it the most spectacular
countryside celebration ever, okay, sis?

572
00:40:22,720 --> 00:40:25,040
A woman? What woman?

573
00:40:29,840 --> 00:40:31,200
No way.

574
00:40:31,280 --> 00:40:34,320
I'm not a virgin anymore.

575
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:36,720
I don't deserve you, really.

576
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:39,600
Pin. Aunt Un.

577
00:40:40,840 --> 00:40:43,000
My bride is here.

578
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:49,720
Pin.

579
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:53,800
I will marry Pinanong.

580
00:40:53,880 --> 00:40:55,000
Mr. Yai?

581
00:40:56,880 --> 00:40:59,760
Mr. Yai,
please don't joke like this with me.

582
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:02,800
Who would joke about
an important thing like this, Auntie?

583
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:04,520
What do you say, Un?

584
00:41:04,600 --> 00:41:06,120
It can't be, Madam.

585
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:10,360
I would never be family
with all of you thieves.

586
00:41:12,520 --> 00:41:14,960
When will karma catch up to you all?

587
00:41:15,040 --> 00:41:17,200
If you want to talk about sins and karma,

588
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:19,320
we would be here all day.

589
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:22,240
But let's just say that

590
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:25,880
Mr. Yai, my handsome boy,

591
00:41:25,960 --> 00:41:28,000
wants to marry your beautiful daughter.

592
00:41:29,560 --> 00:41:31,800
I've prepared the dowry as per the custom

593
00:41:31,880 --> 00:41:34,720
and have been appointed
as a representative elder in proposing.

594
00:41:35,360 --> 00:41:38,280
But you all are being far too difficult.

595
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:42,320
If you prefer a funeral
to an auspicious occasion, so be it.

596
00:41:44,800 --> 00:41:48,760
My dad would rather die
than be disrespected.

597
00:41:49,360 --> 00:41:50,840
Think it through, Aunt Un.

598
00:41:55,840 --> 00:41:57,000
This can't be happening.

599
00:41:57,720 --> 00:41:59,360
Mr. Yai, please stop.

600
00:42:02,360 --> 00:42:07,120
So I have to stand here
to witness a thief proposing to a maid?

601
00:42:08,680 --> 00:42:09,720
I'm going to throw up.

602
00:42:10,400 --> 00:42:12,800
Pin. Why are you playing hard to get?

603
00:42:12,880 --> 00:42:14,880
Just marry him and be done with it.

604
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:19,640
See? Both my soon-to-be
sister-in-law and my sister

605
00:42:19,720 --> 00:42:23,120
have agreed that you're
the most suitable one to be my bride.

606
00:42:24,680 --> 00:42:27,560
All that's left is… is…

607
00:42:27,640 --> 00:42:30,440
my only dear brother.

608
00:42:38,760 --> 00:42:39,760
Hey.

609
00:42:40,360 --> 00:42:41,680
What do you have to say?

610
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:44,440
Uh…

611
00:42:45,960 --> 00:42:47,520
If Mr. Yai truly loves Pin,

612
00:42:48,560 --> 00:42:50,160
I have no objections.

613
00:42:52,880 --> 00:42:54,240
Aunt Un,

614
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:57,520
please let Pin marry Mr. Yai.

615
00:43:04,520 --> 00:43:06,240
Never.

616
00:43:11,200 --> 00:43:15,120
The choice is entirely up to her, Un,

617
00:43:15,680 --> 00:43:17,440
whether she's willing or not.

618
00:43:35,760 --> 00:43:36,760
I'm…

619
00:43:38,760 --> 00:43:40,840
I'm willing to marry him.

620
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:49,720
Pin…

621
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:57,120
What evidence, Mr. Yai?

622
00:43:57,200 --> 00:44:00,040
I suspect that my dad might not have died
from illness, Uncle Pload.

623
00:44:00,800 --> 00:44:03,080
I would never think
of betraying you, Madam.

624
00:44:03,160 --> 00:44:05,680
Then kill Yai for me. Can you do that?

625
00:44:05,760 --> 00:44:09,320
Please welcome Mr. Yai, Chalit,
the only heir to Paisal Farm,

626
00:44:09,400 --> 00:44:12,920
and Pinanong, the beautiful bride.

627
00:44:16,240 --> 00:44:17,080
Aunt Un?

628
00:44:19,400 --> 00:44:20,560
Mom!

629
00:45:00,720 --> 00:45:03,040
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
